Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1} into half moons. Remove the ends from the @courgette{1}, halve lengthways, then slice into 1cm wide half moons. Drain and rinse the @black beans{1%400g can} in a #sieve{}. Halve and deseed the @green chilli{1/2}(deseeded), then finely chop. Zest the @lime{1/2} and keep to one side.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium heat. Add the onion and cook, stirring, until soft, ~{5%minutes}. Add the courgette along with a pinch of @salt{} and cook, stirring, until starting to soften, about ~{3%minutes}. Stir in the chilli and cook for a further ~{1%minute}.

> Add as much or as little chilli as you like!

Stir the @ground cumin{2%tsp} into your veggies, then add the black beans, @tomato passata{1%400ml jar} and a squeeze of lime juice (don't use it all yet!). Season with a pinch of salt and @pepper{}, bring to a simmer and allow to bubble away until slightly thickened, about ~{4-5%minutes}.

While your filling cooks, add a pinch of lime zest to the @soured cream{150%g} and mix with a pinch of salt. Cut the @baby gem lettuce{1} in half lengthways and then finely slice it widthways. Pop the lettuce in a #bowl{} (we'll dress it later). Season with a good pinch of salt and pepper.

Pile some of the courgette mixture onto one half of each @super soft whole wheat tortillas{4}. Grate over some of the @mature cheddar cheese{60%g}. Fold over the other side of the tortilla to make half moon shaped quesadillas. Repeat until you have used up all your mixture - you should make at least two quesadillas per person, but it will depend on how generously you fill them!

Put another frying pan on medium heat (no oil). When hot, fry each quesadilla until golden brown, about ~{2%minutes} each side, careful when you turn them over! Remove to a #plate{} and keep warm under some #foil{} and repeat until you have cooked all your quesadillas. Drizzle over some @olive oil{} and squeeze some of the remaining lime juice over the lettuce. Serve the quesadillas with the zesty sour cream and some baby gem. Enjoy